  "text": "All statistical analyses were performed using SPSS 15. and one-way analysis of variance were used to compare categorical and continuous variables, respectively. To evaluate if respiratory muscle weakness might be associated with worse outcomes, we performed a sensitivity analysis using three successively more stringent definitions for a restrictive pattern that is likely caused by respiratory muscle weakness. Cox proportional hazards models were used to assess the relationship between pulmonary restriction and the outcomes of interest. Patients who developed disease relapse were censored at the time of relapse for the nonrelapse mortality analysis. To account for potential changes in clinical practice over time, we considered the year of transplant as a categorical variable in the analysis. The incidence of developing early respiratory failure and nonrelapse mortality according to lung function parameters were plotted using cumulative incidence curves, with disease relapse treated as a competing event for nonrelapse mortality and all cause mortality treated as a competing event for respiratory failure. Cumulative incidence curves were compared using the methods of Gray [CITATION_1] .",
